4002611a-9be8-41b2-a5f5-4dd021f5a102 To make the drinks, shake or stir together the cranberry juice, lime juice, tequila, and orange liquor in a cocktail shaker filled with ice.

839d7a5d-d33f-439a-9f59-18a23b32b50b Peel the outer leaves from the lemongrass stalks cut off the ends and chop the remaining grass into thin rounds.
839d7a5d-d33f-439a-9f59-18a23b32b50b Place the lemongrass and whole ginger in the bottom of a clean mason jar or similar jar with a tight sealing lid.
839d7a5d-d33f-439a-9f59-18a23b32b50b Pour the tequila over the herbs and shake a few times.
839d7a5d-d33f-439a-9f59-18a23b32b50b Seal the lid tight and store the jar in a cool, dark place for about 2 weeks.
839d7a5d-d33f-439a-9f59-18a23b32b50b Test the flavor of the​ infusion every day, beginning on the fifth day.
839d7a5d-d33f-439a-9f59-18a23b32b50b Once the flavor is to taste, strain the lemongrass and ginger from the tequila.
839d7a5d-d33f-439a-9f59-18a23b32b50b Wash the jar and return the flavored tequila to it.
839d7a5d-d33f-439a-9f59-18a23b32b50b Store as you would any other tequila.

c74ede9f-30ae-4012-93e3-31225770f04f Preheat oven to 350 F. Prepare the muffin tin by lining with baking cups.
c74ede9f-30ae-4012-93e3-31225770f04f In the mixing bowl of a stand mixer, combine cake mix, Margarita mix, egg whites, oil and lime zest. Blend on low for 30 seconds then medium for 2 minutes.
c74ede9f-30ae-4012-93e3-31225770f04f Spoon batter into baking cups, filling about 2/3 full.
c74ede9f-30ae-4012-93e3-31225770f04f Bake 22 to 24 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.
c74ede9f-30ae-4012-93e3-31225770f04f Cool in pans for 5 minutes and then remove from pans and cool completely before frosting.
c74ede9f-30ae-4012-93e3-31225770f04f For icing, beat shortening, butter and lime zest with mixer until smooth.
c74ede9f-30ae-4012-93e3-31225770f04f Gradually add sugar 1 cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
c74ede9f-30ae-4012-93e3-31225770f04f Add tequila and beat until light and fluffy.
c74ede9f-30ae-4012-93e3-31225770f04f Spread icing onto cupcakes. Sprinkle green sanding sugar around the edge of the cupcakes and garnish with additional lime zest.
c74ede9f-30ae-4012-93e3-31225770f04f Cut a small opening at the tip of the Shot Tops Infuser. Place the cut opening into the tequila and squeeze the top to fill. Insert the cut end into the cupcakes. When ready to eat, squeeze the top of Shot Tops Infuser again to infuse cake with tequila.

d90d2b30-3dec-447e-a7da-b6fe8b9ed142 Add a splash of dry vermouth and swirl it around the glass.
d90d2b30-3dec-447e-a7da-b6fe8b9ed142 While the glass is chilling, pour the gin into a mixing glass with ice and stir.
d90d2b30-3dec-447e-a7da-b6fe8b9ed142 Throw away the ice and vermouth.
d90d2b30-3dec-447e-a7da-b6fe8b9ed142 Strain the gin into the prepared cocktail glass.
6ddef970-00c6-4b9d-93a4-24d7e3cbc7ad In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour all of the ingredients.
6ddef970-00c6-4b9d-93a4-24d7e3cbc7ad Shake well.

ab56aa39-382c-49cc-a621-52d1acf4910e Gather the ingredients.
ab56aa39-382c-49cc-a621-52d1acf4910e In a large saucepan on low heat, add the gin and Madeira wine.
ab56aa39-382c-49cc-a621-52d1acf4910e Cut the lemon twists, orange slice, and pineapple chunks. Add them to the punch.
ab56aa39-382c-49cc-a621-52d1acf4910e Stir in the honey and lemon juice, then the cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon, and brown sugar. Continue stirring until the sugar and ground spices are dissolved.
ab56aa39-382c-49cc-a621-52d1acf4910e Simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.
ab56aa39-382c-49cc-a621-52d1acf4910e Strain using a fine-mesh strainer to remove all the whole fruits and spices. Pour the punch into a heat-proof punch bowl. Garnish with orange slices studded with cloves.
ab56aa39-382c-49cc-a621-52d1acf4910e Serve and enjoy!
b0a8e85a-9174-49ee-8db3-e063fad458dc Gather the ingredients.
b0a8e85a-9174-49ee-8db3-e063fad458dc Pour the ingredients into a cocktail shaker with ice cubes.
b0a8e85a-9174-49ee-8db3-e063fad458dc Shake vigorously (more than normal to properly mix the egg and sugar).

4fd9a7f7-b654-4be4-bc75-2a54923705d7 Gather the ingredients.
4fd9a7f7-b654-4be4-bc75-2a54923705d7 Cut the pear and apples into slices.
4fd9a7f7-b654-4be4-bc75-2a54923705d7 Place all pears and apples in the bottom of a clean mason jar or similar jar with a tight sealing lid.
4fd9a7f7-b654-4be4-bc75-2a54923705d7 Pour the gin over the fruit and shake a few times.
4fd9a7f7-b654-4be4-bc75-2a54923705d7 Seal the lid tight and store the jar in a cool, dark place for about 1 week.
4fd9a7f7-b654-4be4-bc75-2a54923705d7 Test the flavor of the infusion daily.
4fd9a7f7-b654-4be4-bc75-2a54923705d7 Once the flavor is to taste, you must strain the fruits from the gin.
4fd9a7f7-b654-4be4-bc75-2a54923705d7 Wash the jar and return the flavored gin to it.
4fd9a7f7-b654-4be4-bc75-2a54923705d7 Store as you do other liquors.

c5fc0f94-4955-440a-9315-4cd6296552b7 Pour all of the ingredients into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
c5fc0f94-4955-440a-9315-4cd6296552b7 Shake well.
c5fc0f94-4955-440a-9315-4cd6296552b7 Strain into a collins or hurricane glass filled with cracked ice.
c5fc0f94-4955-440a-9315-4cd6296552b7 Garnish with a strawberry or cherry. Serve and enjoy.

4699db7a-ba50-4397-ba31-9acc947ca33a Gather the ingredients.
4699db7a-ba50-4397-ba31-9acc947ca33a Pour the light rum, pineapple juice, and cream of coconut into a cocktail shaker filled with ice. For a slightly less sweet colada, squeeze the juice of a lime wedge into the shaker.
4699db7a-ba50-4397-ba31-9acc947ca33a Shake well for at least 30 seconds. When thoroughly shaken, the drink should be creamy with a luscious foam from the pineapple juice.
4699db7a-ba50-4397-ba31-9acc947ca33a Strain into a chilled Mason jar or collins glass. Alternatively, it will fill 1 large or 2 small cocktail glasses.
4699db7a-ba50-4397-ba31-9acc947ca33a Garnish with the pineapple wedge and maraschino cherry.
4699db7a-ba50-4397-ba31-9acc947ca33a Serve and enjoy.

f2b60b12-ca99-42f4-b112-b4929a49c79b Top with cola.
f2b60b12-ca99-42f4-b112-b4929a49c79b Garnish with a lime wedge. Serve and enjoy.
46b522f7-9ed1-4f73-9fce-04227452c4cf Gather the ingredients.
46b522f7-9ed1-4f73-9fce-04227452c4cf Add all of the ingredients to a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
46b522f7-9ed1-4f73-9fce-04227452c4cf Shake well.
46b522f7-9ed1-4f73-9fce-04227452c4cf Strain into a hurricane glass over fresh ice.
46b522f7-9ed1-4f73-9fce-04227452c4cf Garnish with fruit and enjoy.
f8739759-dff6-4b16-9732-fdf8d97534b9 Gather the ingredients.
f8739759-dff6-4b16-9732-fdf8d97534b9 Rim a tall glass with graham crackers if you like and drizzle chocolate syrup inside the glass. Place it in the freezer.
f8739759-dff6-4b16-9732-fdf8d97534b9 In a blender, combine the liquors and ice cream and blend until smooth. To create a thicker shake, add more ice cream. If it's too thick, add more RumChata.
f8739759-dff6-4b16-9732-fdf8d97534b9 Pour the blended shake into the prepared frozen glass.
f8739759-dff6-4b16-9732-fdf8d97534b9 Garnish with a toasted marshmallow and chocolate shavings.
f8739759-dff6-4b16-9732-fdf8d97534b9 Serve and enjoy!

dd3f7a09-2ac5-429e-b516-a4ddddce1cad Combine all of the ingredients and pour the punch over cracked ice.
dd3f7a09-2ac5-429e-b516-a4ddddce1cad Allow it to stand for two hours.
dd3f7a09-2ac5-429e-b516-a4ddddce1cad Add more ice and garnish with gardenias or slices of citrus fruit.
dd3f7a09-2ac5-429e-b516-a4ddddce1cad Serve and enjoy!

0cfab6d7-38bf-491a-88c9-2bef45ab84a9 Cut half of a lime into small wedges.
0cfab6d7-38bf-491a-88c9-2bef45ab84a9 Place the lime and sugar into an old-fashioned glass and muddle well.
0cfab6d7-38bf-491a-88c9-2bef45ab84a9 Top the drink with cachaça, stir well.
0cfab6d7-38bf-491a-88c9-2bef45ab84a9 Fill the glass with small ice cubes or cracked ice, stir again, and garnish with a lime wheel. Serve and enjoy.

f3d9a5e3-6c6b-4b8e-a1b5-c001f0010a60 Add the sugar, mint leaves, and a splash of club soda to a highball glass.
f3d9a5e3-6c6b-4b8e-a1b5-c001f0010a60 Muddle just enough to dissolve the sugar and release the flavor of the mint.
f3d9a5e3-6c6b-4b8e-a1b5-c001f0010a60 Squeeze the juice from the two halves of lime into the glass. Drop one squeezed half into the glass.
f3d9a5e3-6c6b-4b8e-a1b5-c001f0010a60 Add the rum and stir well.
f3d9a5e3-6c6b-4b8e-a1b5-c001f0010a60 Fill the glass with ice cubes. Top with club soda and garnish with a mint sprig.
03ee7bc1-3680-40a7-b1d7-33627ee207c0 Gather the ingredients.
03ee7bc1-3680-40a7-b1d7-33627ee207c0 Pour the ingredients into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
03ee7bc1-3680-40a7-b1d7-33627ee207c0 Shake well.
03ee7bc1-3680-40a7-b1d7-33627ee207c0 Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
03ee7bc1-3680-40a7-b1d7-33627ee207c0 Garnish with a pineapple wedge and/or coconut flakes.
03ee7bc1-3680-40a7-b1d7-33627ee207c0 Enjoy!
16ee973e-0285-4c3e-b943-dc69ab30b2d1 Gather the ingredients.
16ee973e-0285-4c3e-b943-dc69ab30b2d1 Add the ingredients to a cocktail shaker with ice cubes.
16ee973e-0285-4c3e-b943-dc69ab30b2d1 Shake well.
16ee973e-0285-4c3e-b943-dc69ab30b2d1 Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
16ee973e-0285-4c3e-b943-dc69ab30b2d1 Serve and enjoy.
cbf97d3c-6b73-4a19-baac-9410eab10cc5 Gather the ingredients.
cbf97d3c-6b73-4a19-baac-9410eab10cc5 In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the rum, maraschino liqueur, and grapefruit and lime juices. Add the simple syrup if desired.
cbf97d3c-6b73-4a19-baac-9410eab10cc5 Shake well.
cbf97d3c-6b73-4a19-baac-9410eab10cc5 Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
cbf97d3c-6b73-4a19-baac-9410eab10cc5 Garnish with a lime wheel. Serve and enjoy.
ee0e98d0-6417-4789-99c0-13f375605cac Gather the ingredients.
ee0e98d0-6417-4789-99c0-13f375605cac Add 1 cup fresh mint leaves and sugar to a large pitcher or mixing bowl. Using a wooden spoon, lightly crush the mint until it’s aromatic.
ee0e98d0-6417-4789-99c0-13f375605cac Add the rum and lime juice and stir well until the sugar completely dissolves.
ee0e98d0-6417-4789-99c0-13f375605cac Add the pomegranate juice and club soda. Stir again and add the pomegranate seeds.
ee0e98d0-6417-4789-99c0-13f375605cac Serve in glasses filled with ice.
eb1cf2d6-7e75-4c70-b920-e198dd170a6c Gather the ingredients.
eb1cf2d6-7e75-4c70-b920-e198dd170a6c Place the sugar, butter, and spices into the bottom of an Irish coffee glass or mug and mix well or muddle.
eb1cf2d6-7e75-4c70-b920-e198dd170a6c Pour in the rum and top it with hot water.
eb1cf2d6-7e75-4c70-b920-e198dd170a6c Stir. Serve and enjoy!
2521959d-e555-4405-aefd-ec4ee9164200 Gather the ingredients.
2521959d-e555-4405-aefd-ec4ee9164200 Pour the ingredients into a mixing glass filled with ice cubes. Shake well.
2521959d-e555-4405-aefd-ec4ee9164200 Strain into a highball glass filled with ice cubes.
2521959d-e555-4405-aefd-ec4ee9164200 Top with club soda if you like and garnish with seasonal fruits.
2521959d-e555-4405-aefd-ec4ee9164200 Serve and enjoy!
73962dd3-c52e-4fa7-b201-acbbe2f6b015 Gather the ingredients.
73962dd3-c52e-4fa7-b201-acbbe2f6b015 Put 1/4 cup to 1/2 cup of ice in the blender container.
73962dd3-c52e-4fa7-b201-acbbe2f6b015 Add the white rum, Kahlúa, banana-flavored liqueur, light cream, whole milk, and ripe banana and cover. Blend until smooth, increasing the speed as necessary to thoroughly pulverize the ice.
73962dd3-c52e-4fa7-b201-acbbe2f6b015 Pour the drink into a (preferably chilled) small hurricane glass, martini glass, or other cocktail glass.
73962dd3-c52e-4fa7-b201-acbbe2f6b015 Cut a slit halfway through a banana wheel and hang it on the rim of the glass. Top with a maraschino cherry if desired.
73962dd3-c52e-4fa7-b201-acbbe2f6b015 Serve immediately and enjoy.
ec2d5416-5e01-4d3d-ac7f-ac480ba6d24f Gather the ingredients.
ec2d5416-5e01-4d3d-ac7f-ac480ba6d24f Squeeze the juice of half a lime into a cocktail shaker with ice.
ec2d5416-5e01-4d3d-ac7f-ac480ba6d24f Add the orange juice, both rums, and Galliano.
ec2d5416-5e01-4d3d-ac7f-ac480ba6d24f Shake well.
ec2d5416-5e01-4d3d-ac7f-ac480ba6d24f Strain into a collins glass filled with crushed ice.
ec2d5416-5e01-4d3d-ac7f-ac480ba6d24f Garnish with a cherry and a sprig of mint, if you like.
ec2d5416-5e01-4d3d-ac7f-ac480ba6d24f Serve and enjoy!
31e7243f-3931-4534-947b-747aeee33bb9 Gather the ingredients.
31e7243f-3931-4534-947b-747aeee33bb9 In a blender, add the ice and all of the liquid ingredients. Blend until smooth.
31e7243f-3931-4534-947b-747aeee33bb9 Pour into a chilled hurricane glass. Serve and enjoy.
693d3fbd-3c44-4d1b-9cd6-5c0d9277032e Stir the liquors in a collins glass.
693d3fbd-3c44-4d1b-9cd6-5c0d9277032e Add sugar and stir again (but not too well).
693d3fbd-3c44-4d1b-9cd6-5c0d9277032e Add ice, then cola.
693d3fbd-3c44-4d1b-9cd6-5c0d9277032e Stir three times and serve with a straw.
870b77b3-4e41-491c-a806-635537e48510 Gather the ingredients.
870b77b3-4e41-491c-a806-635537e48510 Pour the ingredients into a cocktail shaker with ice. If using, save the 151 rum for a float.
870b77b3-4e41-491c-a806-635537e48510 Shake well.
870b77b3-4e41-491c-a806-635537e48510 Strain into a tall glass filled with fresh ice.
870b77b3-4e41-491c-a806-635537e48510 Optionally, float the high-proof rum on top of the drink by slowly pouring it over the back of a bar spoon.
870b77b3-4e41-491c-a806-635537e48510 Garnish with mint and seasonal fruits.
bde65d17-c6d9-4512-a0c3-5fb2155ac103 Put the mint leaves into a Collins glass and squeeze the lime juice over them.
bde65d17-c6d9-4512-a0c3-5fb2155ac103 Add the powdered sugar and then muddle the mint, lime juice, and sugar together.
bde65d17-c6d9-4512-a0c3-5fb2155ac103 Add crushed ice.
bde65d17-c6d9-4512-a0c3-5fb2155ac103 Stir in the rum and top off with the club soda.
bde65d17-c6d9-4512-a0c3-5fb2155ac103 Garnish with a mint sprig.
95d7e101-657d-459e-b5d3-73a056ae723c Gather the ingredients.
95d7e101-657d-459e-b5d3-73a056ae723c In a blender, add the ice, rum, triple sec, lime juice, and simple syrup.
95d7e101-657d-459e-b5d3-73a056ae723c Blend until smooth.
95d7e101-657d-459e-b5d3-73a056ae723c Pour into a chilled collins glass.
95d7e101-657d-459e-b5d3-73a056ae723c Garnish with a lime wedge.
95d7e101-657d-459e-b5d3-73a056ae723c Serve and enjoy!
629c9598-efb6-48cb-ac03-561278db421a Gather the ingredients.
629c9598-efb6-48cb-ac03-561278db421a Pour the ingredients into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
629c9598-efb6-48cb-ac03-561278db421a Shake well.
629c9598-efb6-48cb-ac03-561278db421a Strain into a shot glass.
629c9598-efb6-48cb-ac03-561278db421a Serve and get it down!
0eeb9f47-174b-4a62-947b-83b44e31a3c2 Gather the ingredients.
0eeb9f47-174b-4a62-947b-83b44e31a3c2 Pour all of the ingredients into a blender.
0eeb9f47-174b-4a62-947b-83b44e31a3c2 Blend on low speed for a few seconds, then at high speed until smooth.
0eeb9f47-174b-4a62-947b-83b44e31a3c2 Pour the contents into a chilled hurricane glass.
0eeb9f47-174b-4a62-947b-83b44e31a3c2 Garnish with a maraschino cherry.
0eeb9f47-174b-4a62-947b-83b44e31a3c2 Serve and enjoy.
0b114a48-6192-4dd6-99ae-11bc162a80a7 Gather the ingredients.
0b114a48-6192-4dd6-99ae-11bc162a80a7 Squeeze the juice of half a lime into a collins glass or highball glass.
0b114a48-6192-4dd6-99ae-11bc162a80a7 Add ice cubes and pour the rum into the glass.
0b114a48-6192-4dd6-99ae-11bc162a80a7 Fill with cola and stir well.
0b114a48-6192-4dd6-99ae-11bc162a80a7 Serve and enjoy!
56a71bad-e8ca-450f-b9fb-d71c534fb2d9 Gather the ingredients.
56a71bad-e8ca-450f-b9fb-d71c534fb2d9 Pour the ingredients into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
56a71bad-e8ca-450f-b9fb-d71c534fb2d9 Shake well.
56a71bad-e8ca-450f-b9fb-d71c534fb2d9 Strain into an old-fashioned glass filled with ice.
56a71bad-e8ca-450f-b9fb-d71c534fb2d9 Serve and enjoy!
f9a9b362-0680-45ac-a2b0-ceaafb12a6e6 Rim a chilled cocktail glass with sugar.
f9a9b362-0680-45ac-a2b0-ceaafb12a6e6 Pour the ingredients into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
f9a9b362-0680-45ac-a2b0-ceaafb12a6e6 Shake well.
f9a9b362-0680-45ac-a2b0-ceaafb12a6e6 Strain into the prepared glass.
f9a9b362-0680-45ac-a2b0-ceaafb12a6e6 Garnish with an orange peel spiral.
cbc02373-fe7c-4c2b-ac98-1ea687a1d338 Pour all of the liquid ingredients into a blender.
cbc02373-fe7c-4c2b-ac98-1ea687a1d338 Add ice.
cbc02373-fe7c-4c2b-ac98-1ea687a1d338 Blend on a fast speed for about 5-10 seconds.
cbc02373-fe7c-4c2b-ac98-1ea687a1d338 Pour into a hurricane or margarita glass.
cbc02373-fe7c-4c2b-ac98-1ea687a1d338 Garnish with a cherry.
28869a81-f1dc-4215-ab5f-9bbc9a0ed2ef Gather the ingredients.
28869a81-f1dc-4215-ab5f-9bbc9a0ed2ef Build the ingredients in a highball glass filled with ice cubes.
28869a81-f1dc-4215-ab5f-9bbc9a0ed2ef Garnish with the lime wedge.
28869a81-f1dc-4215-ab5f-9bbc9a0ed2ef Serve and enjoy!
29c7d20d-2ef4-4b99-9e9d-576aafdc9bcf Gather the ingredients.
29c7d20d-2ef4-4b99-9e9d-576aafdc9bcf Separate the egg into two bowls.
29c7d20d-2ef4-4b99-9e9d-576aafdc9bcf With a hand mixer, beat the yolk until stiff.
29c7d20d-2ef4-4b99-9e9d-576aafdc9bcf Beat the white with 1 teaspoon sugar until peaks form.
29c7d20d-2ef4-4b99-9e9d-576aafdc9bcf Slowly fold the white and yolk together using a spoon.
29c7d20d-2ef4-4b99-9e9d-576aafdc9bcf In a separate bowl, beat the cream with the almond and vanilla extracts and the remaining teaspoon of sugar until stiff.
29c7d20d-2ef4-4b99-9e9d-576aafdc9bcf Slowly fold the cream into the egg mixture.
29c7d20d-2ef4-4b99-9e9d-576aafdc9bcf Add the rum and stir gently.
29c7d20d-2ef4-4b99-9e9d-576aafdc9bcf Refrigerate overnight, or serve immediately over ice in a punch or martini glass.
29c7d20d-2ef4-4b99-9e9d-576aafdc9bcf Garnish with grated nutmeg and cinnamon. Serve and enjoy.
ada8fe6c-9aa0-4c65-92ea-117dcea13290 Build the rum, curacao, lime juice and bitters in a highball glass filled with ice.
ada8fe6c-9aa0-4c65-92ea-117dcea13290 Top with ginger beer.
ada8fe6c-9aa0-4c65-92ea-117dcea13290 Garnish with the orange and lime.
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Prepare the spice mixture
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 In a medium size soup pot over medium-high heat, add 1/4 cup vegetable oil.
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Add meat and lightly brown for 6 to 8 minutes.
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Add 1 tablespoon of flour and cook for 1 minute and remove meat mixture from the pot.
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Reheat the same pot by turning it up to a medium-high heat.
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Add 1/4 cup vegetable oil, minced onions, habanero, ginger, and garlic.
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Slowly saute for 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture is completely tender and has no crunch.
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Add the prepared spice mixture to the onion and lightly toast for 3 to 4 minutes or until the mixture is golden brown.
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Remove the pot from the heat, add meat and rum then return to the stove top and cook until mixture is dry. (Beware, the rum could ignite like a flambé, make sure that you are standing away from the pot as you place it back on the flame.)
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Add beer, chicken broth, tomatoes, and salsa verde and bring to a boil.
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
74dcceef-a4df-47a2-a69e-8ceb8d6871e4 Stir in chopped cilantro, garnish and serve.
0effd0e7-e5f8-4371-805b-d7a059f12617 Gather the ingredients.
0effd0e7-e5f8-4371-805b-d7a059f12617 In a large punch bowl or pitcher, combine the rum, red wine, lime juice, triple sec, simple syrup, and lime and orange slices.
0effd0e7-e5f8-4371-805b-d7a059f12617 Cover with plastic wrap and place in the refrigerator for at least two hours before serving (overnight is better).
0effd0e7-e5f8-4371-805b-d7a059f12617 Serve over ice in punch glasses and enjoy!
c907511a-89fc-462a-abe8-aee13fea453e Pour the ingredients into a cocktail shaker with ice.
c907511a-89fc-462a-abe8-aee13fea453e Shake well.
c907511a-89fc-462a-abe8-aee13fea453e Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
c907511a-89fc-462a-abe8-aee13fea453e Garnish with the lemon twist.
62b8422e-5a54-4687-8a6c-f21bf4834792 Gather the ingredients.
62b8422e-5a54-4687-8a6c-f21bf4834792 Pour the rums, juices, and syrups into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
62b8422e-5a54-4687-8a6c-f21bf4834792 Shake well.
62b8422e-5a54-4687-8a6c-f21bf4834792 Strain into a collins glass filled with ice.
62b8422e-5a54-4687-8a6c-f21bf4834792 Garnish with an orange slice and cherry skewer. Serve and enjoy.
7a6e76de-9e53-4020-a6c6-efc203cb85ed Gather the ingredients.
7a6e76de-9e53-4020-a6c6-efc203cb85ed In a punch bowl, add large pieces of ice to fill it just over halfway.
7a6e76de-9e53-4020-a6c6-efc203cb85ed Add the wine, mango rum, peach schnapps, all the citrus juices, and lemon-lime soda.
7a6e76de-9e53-4020-a6c6-efc203cb85ed Serve in glasses garnished with slices of white peach and enjoy!
6e8df02c-351f-4767-b772-3d8bd7bce7d2 Gather the ingredients.
6e8df02c-351f-4767-b772-3d8bd7bce7d2 Rim a coupe glass with banana dust.
6e8df02c-351f-4767-b772-3d8bd7bce7d2 Pour the rum, syrup, lime, and bitters into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
6e8df02c-351f-4767-b772-3d8bd7bce7d2 Shake well.
6e8df02c-351f-4767-b772-3d8bd7bce7d2 Strain into the prepared coupe glass.
6e8df02c-351f-4767-b772-3d8bd7bce7d2 Serve and enjoy!
448e2bc5-3dca-437a-bcba-3581d9667519 Gather the ingredients.
448e2bc5-3dca-437a-bcba-3581d9667519 In a cocktail shaker, thoroughly muddle the fruit with the absinthe, cachaça, brandy, and orange liqueur.
448e2bc5-3dca-437a-bcba-3581d9667519 Pour everything (including the ice) into a wine glass.
448e2bc5-3dca-437a-bcba-3581d9667519 Float red wine on top of the cocktail by slowly pouring it over the back of a bar spoon.
448e2bc5-3dca-437a-bcba-3581d9667519 Serve and enjoy.
1e5b45ef-f1c8-4ff8-ba12-bfaf7e9c118b Gather the ingredients.
1e5b45ef-f1c8-4ff8-ba12-bfaf7e9c118b In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour all of the ingredients.
1e5b45ef-f1c8-4ff8-ba12-bfaf7e9c118b Shake well.
1e5b45ef-f1c8-4ff8-ba12-bfaf7e9c118b Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
1e5b45ef-f1c8-4ff8-ba12-bfaf7e9c118b Serve and enjoy!
77e63afc-7a4c-428e-859d-e67a7aa9066e Gather the ingredients.
77e63afc-7a4c-428e-859d-e67a7aa9066e Fill a shot glass 3/4 full with amaretto.
77e63afc-7a4c-428e-859d-e67a7aa9066e Slowly float the overproof rum on top to fill the shot glass by pouring it over the back of a bar spoon.
77e63afc-7a4c-428e-859d-e67a7aa9066e Fill a pint glass halfway with beer.
77e63afc-7a4c-428e-859d-e67a7aa9066e Ignite the contents of the shot glass.
77e63afc-7a4c-428e-859d-e67a7aa9066e Blow out the flame, drop the shot glass into the beer, and drink in one gulp.
e86706fb-5d89-4fa7-92d6-5f45e97f4500 Gather the ingredients.
e86706fb-5d89-4fa7-92d6-5f45e97f4500 Pour the rum, pineapple juice, orange juice, and cream of coconut into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
e86706fb-5d89-4fa7-92d6-5f45e97f4500 Shake well.
e86706fb-5d89-4fa7-92d6-5f45e97f4500 Strain into a chilled highball glass filled with fresh ice.
e86706fb-5d89-4fa7-92d6-5f45e97f4500 Garnish with a pineapple wedge and sprinkle the Painkiller with grated nutmeg on top.
e86706fb-5d89-4fa7-92d6-5f45e97f4500 Serve and enjoy.
4c4acc6b-2a61-4d28-ba94-09c7b64b302f In a cocktail shaker, combine the rum, juice, sugar, and liqueurs and filled with ice.
4c4acc6b-2a61-4d28-ba94-09c7b64b302f Shake well.
4c4acc6b-2a61-4d28-ba94-09c7b64b302f Strain into a cocktail glass.
4c4acc6b-2a61-4d28-ba94-09c7b64b302f Add dashes of bitters on top.
56e644a2-80ea-42b0-8fe8-25af29db241a Gather the ingredients.
56e644a2-80ea-42b0-8fe8-25af29db241a In a collins glass filled with ice, build the ingredients by first pouring the rum and amaretto.
56e644a2-80ea-42b0-8fe8-25af29db241a Top the drink off with cola.
56e644a2-80ea-42b0-8fe8-25af29db241a Stir well and garnish with a cherry or lime wedge.
56e644a2-80ea-42b0-8fe8-25af29db241a Serve and enjoy!
ec6c26b1-5ebc-4e7d-9c26-54215a041965 Gather the ingredients.
ec6c26b1-5ebc-4e7d-9c26-54215a041965 In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the rum, lime juice, and grenadine.
ec6c26b1-5ebc-4e7d-9c26-54215a041965 Shake well.
ec6c26b1-5ebc-4e7d-9c26-54215a041965 Strain into a chilled cocktail glass. Serve and enjoy.
18bd8b76-02b8-4a51-b2d4-514ab228831e Pour all ingredients (except the soda) into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
18bd8b76-02b8-4a51-b2d4-514ab228831e Shake vigorously (at least 30 seconds).
18bd8b76-02b8-4a51-b2d4-514ab228831e Strain into a chilled collins glass.
18bd8b76-02b8-4a51-b2d4-514ab228831e Top with club soda.
063c38f3-57b6-4740-ac5a-c2874ca77d7d Gather the ingredients.
063c38f3-57b6-4740-ac5a-c2874ca77d7d If desired, rim a chilled cocktail glass with sugar: Dip the rim into a shallow dish of pumpkin liqueur or wipe the rim with a lime wedge, then roll the wet rim in a small pile of sugar.
063c38f3-57b6-4740-ac5a-c2874ca77d7d In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the pumpkin liqueur, spiced rum, milk, and cream.
063c38f3-57b6-4740-ac5a-c2874ca77d7d Shake well to ensure the dairy is fully mixed into the drink.
063c38f3-57b6-4740-ac5a-c2874ca77d7d Strain into the prepared glass.
063c38f3-57b6-4740-ac5a-c2874ca77d7d Sprinkle the top with a freshly ground cinnamon to garnish.
063c38f3-57b6-4740-ac5a-c2874ca77d7d Serve and enjoy!
79e238c5-a748-4910-ae2b-5bdff8c3b3e1 Gather the ingredients.
79e238c5-a748-4910-ae2b-5bdff8c3b3e1 In a blender, add the ice, coconut milk, banana, Irish cream, and rum.
79e238c5-a748-4910-ae2b-5bdff8c3b3e1 Blend for 15 to 20 seconds, or until smooth.
79e238c5-a748-4910-ae2b-5bdff8c3b3e1 Pour into a tall glass or large margarita glass.
79e238c5-a748-4910-ae2b-5bdff8c3b3e1 Garnish with whipped cream and toasted coconut.
79e238c5-a748-4910-ae2b-5bdff8c3b3e1 Serve and enjoy!
498e1652-29b2-48ab-973e-5ed05a99f384 Gather the ingredients.
498e1652-29b2-48ab-973e-5ed05a99f384 In a highball glass, muddle the salsa, bell pepper slices, lime wedges, chile pepper, and cilantro.
498e1652-29b2-48ab-973e-5ed05a99f384 Fill the glass with ice and add the vodka, green vegetable juice, sauces, and seasonings.
498e1652-29b2-48ab-973e-5ed05a99f384 Stir very well or mix by rolling the drink between two glasses.
498e1652-29b2-48ab-973e-5ed05a99f384 Garnish with celery and a lime wedge.
498e1652-29b2-48ab-973e-5ed05a99f384 Serve and enjoy!
c285b82b-a8b7-47a0-a7c3-77698ae39b2a Gather the ingredients.
c285b82b-a8b7-47a0-a7c3-77698ae39b2a Skewer three cranberries and dust them with sugar. Gently tap off any excess sugar and set aside.
c285b82b-a8b7-47a0-a7c3-77698ae39b2a In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the citrus vodka, white cranberry juice, elderflower liqueur, and lemon juice. Shake well.
c285b82b-a8b7-47a0-a7c3-77698ae39b2a Strain into a chilled cocktail glass and garnish with the cranberry skewer.
c285b82b-a8b7-47a0-a7c3-77698ae39b2a Serve and enjoy!
457a8a3b-6952-4d38-abfb-6869bd847860 Gather the ingredients and tools.
457a8a3b-6952-4d38-abfb-6869bd847860 Secure your watermelon on the table using towels or cloth napkins to keep it from rolling. Draw a circle on the top side of the watermelon with a marker. Make sure it is slightly larger than the widest part of the vodka bottle's neck.
457a8a3b-6952-4d38-abfb-6869bd847860 Cut around the circle with a large knife, digging deep into the melon's flesh. Remove this chunk of rind and flesh.
457a8a3b-6952-4d38-abfb-6869bd847860 Use a spoon to scoop out enough melon so the bottle's neck can fit inside the hole. You want to go deep, but will also be able to gently push the bottle in further.
457a8a3b-6952-4d38-abfb-6869bd847860 Open the bottle of vodka and quickly place it upside down in the hole of the watermelon. It should fit securely and be able to stabilize the bottle.
457a8a3b-6952-4d38-abfb-6869bd847860 When you're ready, quickly remove the vodka bottle. Be ready to use your finger or a towel as a stopper as you bring the bottle upright to prevent spills.
457a8a3b-6952-4d38-abfb-6869bd847860 Place your vodka-infused watermelon in the refrigerator to chill for at least a few hours. When ready to serve, simply cut the watermelon into slices as normal.
1506e03b-4b2d-4f59-b2e1-ea931a5b0a5a Gather the ingredients.
1506e03b-4b2d-4f59-b2e1-ea931a5b0a5a In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, combine all of the ingredients.
1506e03b-4b2d-4f59-b2e1-ea931a5b0a5a Shake well.
1506e03b-4b2d-4f59-b2e1-ea931a5b0a5a Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
1506e03b-4b2d-4f59-b2e1-ea931a5b0a5a Garnish with a lemon zest.
0126f7f2-a9ff-4ca5-9769-631c40584e51 Gather the ingredients.
0126f7f2-a9ff-4ca5-9769-631c40584e51 To rim the cocktail glass, begin by rolling the rim in a shallow dish of caramel syrup.
0126f7f2-a9ff-4ca5-9769-631c40584e51 Roll the glass in a dish of salt, coating it lightly all the way around.
0126f7f2-a9ff-4ca5-9769-631c40584e51 If you want to drizzle caramel inside the glass, hold it upright over the sink to catch any caramel drips. Lightly drizzle caramel webbing inside the glass. Immediately place the glass in the freezer so the caramel sets up while you mix the drink.
0126f7f2-a9ff-4ca5-9769-631c40584e51 In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the vodka, caramel syrup, and Irish cream.
0126f7f2-a9ff-4ca5-9769-631c40584e51 Shake well.
0126f7f2-a9ff-4ca5-9769-631c40584e51 Remove the glass from the freezer and strain the drink into it.
0126f7f2-a9ff-4ca5-9769-631c40584e51 Garnish with a caramel candy.
0126f7f2-a9ff-4ca5-9769-631c40584e51 Serve and enjoy!
0ca88361-356d-4705-836f-8f27953cb55a Gather the ingredients.
0ca88361-356d-4705-836f-8f27953cb55a In a rocks glass filled with ice, build the grapefruit wedges, vodka, and soda.
0ca88361-356d-4705-836f-8f27953cb55a Garnish with a sprig of thyme.
0ca88361-356d-4705-836f-8f27953cb55a Serve and enjoy!
f29fd81a-3f53-4dd4-a909-cc437bf619d7 Gather the ingredients.
f29fd81a-3f53-4dd4-a909-cc437bf619d7 To make the spiced tahini simple syrup, add the sugar and water to a pot and heat on a medium flame just until the sugar dissolves. Whisk in the ground ginger, ground cinnamon, sesame paste and salt, until thoroughly combined. Set aside to cool.
f29fd81a-3f53-4dd4-a909-cc437bf619d7 To make the cocktail, add the vodka, 2 oz. of the tahini syrup, milk or cream, chocolate liqueur and coffee liqueur to a cocktail shaker. Fill the shaker with ice and give it a heavy shake. Pour into chilled cocktail glasses ad sprinkle the crumbled halva candy on top.
934be7e5-e3a9-4f13-b5a5-21a89b970a10 Gather the ingredients.
934be7e5-e3a9-4f13-b5a5-21a89b970a10 Muddle the watermelon and parsley in a cocktail shaker.
934be7e5-e3a9-4f13-b5a5-21a89b970a10 Add remaining ingredients and ice, and shake well.
934be7e5-e3a9-4f13-b5a5-21a89b970a10 Double strain into an ice-filled collins glass that is half-rimmed with sugar.
934be7e5-e3a9-4f13-b5a5-21a89b970a10 Top with sparkling pink lemonade and garnish with assorted fruits.
934be7e5-e3a9-4f13-b5a5-21a89b970a10 Serve and enjoy!
3177cf86-5831-496c-a511-5c9fd1793d3d Gather the ingredients.
3177cf86-5831-496c-a511-5c9fd1793d3d Rim a cocktail glass with colored sugar or candy sprinkles: Begin by wetting the rim with a quick dip in a dish of Irish cream or amaretto, then roll it in a dish of the sugar or sprinkles.
3177cf86-5831-496c-a511-5c9fd1793d3d In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the vanilla vodka, amaretto, and Irish cream.
3177cf86-5831-496c-a511-5c9fd1793d3d Shake well.
3177cf86-5831-496c-a511-5c9fd1793d3d Strain into the prepared glass.
3177cf86-5831-496c-a511-5c9fd1793d3d Serve and enjoy!

da56e0dd-25a8-442d-885a-f94bfd506d14 In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the vodka, apple cider, and lime juice.
da56e0dd-25a8-442d-885a-f94bfd506d14 Shake well.
da56e0dd-25a8-442d-885a-f94bfd506d14 Strain into a copper mug filled with fresh ice.

b2788b34-5eb9-460a-ba86-a2a1e6ff739c Muddle three slices of cucumber with hot sauce, lime juice, simple syrup and vodka in the bottom of a cocktail shaker.
b2788b34-5eb9-460a-ba86-a2a1e6ff739c Add ice and shake well.
b2788b34-5eb9-460a-ba86-a2a1e6ff739c Strain into an old-fashioned glass filled with fresh ice.
b2788b34-5eb9-460a-ba86-a2a1e6ff739c Top with club soda.
b2788b34-5eb9-460a-ba86-a2a1e6ff739c Garnish with a cucumber slice and add an extra dash of hot sauce.

b69a639a-5c2a-41ef-a629-7b4713c951ab Fill a chilled highball glass with crushed ice and add the vodka.
b69a639a-5c2a-41ef-a629-7b4713c951ab Top with lemonade to just below the rim, then add the raspberry liqueur.
b69a639a-5c2a-41ef-a629-7b4713c951ab Garnish with honeydew melon balls.

58ba69a7-7c04-4831-a10b-9e12993d053d Fill with tonic and stir.
58ba69a7-7c04-4831-a10b-9e12993d053d Garnish with a lime wedge.
58ba69a7-7c04-4831-a10b-9e12993d053d Serve and enjoy!
7e0e03ac-e3fc-4f60-ab61-a1b50e746761 Gather the ingredients.
7e0e03ac-e3fc-4f60-ab61-a1b50e746761 Pour the ingredients into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
7e0e03ac-e3fc-4f60-ab61-a1b50e746761 Shake well.
7e0e03ac-e3fc-4f60-ab61-a1b50e746761 Strain into an old-fashioned glass filled with fresh ice.
5eaba8c7-c8fe-40b2-8001-6e6c4a784b6e Gather the ingredients.
5eaba8c7-c8fe-40b2-8001-6e6c4a784b6e In a clean, quart-sized infusion jar with a tight seal, place the cubed watermelon.
5eaba8c7-c8fe-40b2-8001-6e6c4a784b6e Pour the vodka over the fruit and shake a few times.
5eaba8c7-c8fe-40b2-8001-6e6c4a784b6e Seal the lid and store the jar in a cool, dark place for 4 to 6 days. Shake it once or twice a day. Beginning on the third day, test the flavor of the infusion daily.
5eaba8c7-c8fe-40b2-8001-6e6c4a784b6e Once the watermelon flavor is to your taste, strain the watermelon from the vodka. You may need to strain twice or use a cheesecloth to remove all of the fruit and seeds.
5eaba8c7-c8fe-40b2-8001-6e6c4a784b6e Wash the jar and return the flavored vodka to it. Store as you would any other vodka.
5eaba8c7-c8fe-40b2-8001-6e6c4a784b6e Mix the watermelon vodka into cocktails and enjoy!

a0b46c52-aed3-4b18-b73c-8e3a24942f4c Stir well.

dd4a9b2a-8eaa-4e36-bcdf-8b6ec5db07d0 Shake well to achieve good temperature and the characteristic frothy texture on top.

da5f7365-a9ea-4b11-8f67-df0b6110a61f Rim a cocktail glass with cocoa: Wet the rim by dipping it in a small dish of the chocolate liqueur, then dip or roll it in a dish of cocoa powder.

a6b06f2a-6b31-4e0b-aa18-93e57b16c76d Add the fresh cranberries to a small saucepan. Turn on the heat and add the granulated sugar and water. Stir to combine and allow to come to a boil. Once the cranberries are soft (about 5 to 10 minutes), turn off the heat. Let cool to lukewarm. Strain the cranberries over a fine-mesh sieve. Allow the cranberry mixture to completely cool before making the cocktails.
a6b06f2a-6b31-4e0b-aa18-93e57b16c76d Stir the fresh cranberry juice, lime juice, and vodka in a large pitcher. Slowly add the ginger beer and gently stir. If making a single-serve cocktail, use about 2 ounces of vodka, 1 tablespoon of fresh lime juice, and top with ginger beer.
a6b06f2a-6b31-4e0b-aa18-93e57b16c76d Make sure to serve over ice in copper mugs. They not only look pretty but keep the cocktail super cold. Garnish with lime wedges and fresh cranberries.
f2d6be55-bba9-4622-b967-72c8fec56ff0 Gather the ingredients.
f2d6be55-bba9-4622-b967-72c8fec56ff0 Shake the ingredients with ice in a cocktail shaker.
f2d6be55-bba9-4622-b967-72c8fec56ff0 Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
f2d6be55-bba9-4622-b967-72c8fec56ff0 Garnish with an orange peel.

521494e4-f58b-4035-9496-e31dee093c44 Garnish with a cherry and orange slice. Enjoy.

5e8d7e35-e5cb-4497-828f-da3bd2dc2561 In a cocktail shaker filled with ice cubes, pour all of the ingredients.

5e8d7e35-e5cb-4497-828f-da3bd2dc2561 Strain into a highball glass.
5e8d7e35-e5cb-4497-828f-da3bd2dc2561 Garnish with the orange slice and maraschino cherry. Serve and enjoy.
d9a6f802-38f8-496d-ab68-dc0e3e5de130 Gather the ingredients.
d9a6f802-38f8-496d-ab68-dc0e3e5de130 Build the liquid ingredients in a highball glass over ice cubes. Start by pouring the vodka, and then add the tomato juice, lemon juice, and the dash of Worcheshire sauce.
d9a6f802-38f8-496d-ab68-dc0e3e5de130 Add the celery salt, pepper, and hot sauce to taste. If using, add the horseradish.
d9a6f802-38f8-496d-ab68-dc0e3e5de130 Stir well, or try rolling the drink.
d9a6f802-38f8-496d-ab68-dc0e3e5de130 Taste and adjust the seasonings to your liking.
d9a6f802-38f8-496d-ab68-dc0e3e5de130 Garnish with a lemon wedge and celery stalk or pickle.
d9a6f802-38f8-496d-ab68-dc0e3e5de130 Serve and enjoy.
8547cdd2-d0a2-4b58-9f79-0635f2b7ae1a Gather the ingredients.
8547cdd2-d0a2-4b58-9f79-0635f2b7ae1a Trim off and discard the ends of the cucumber and peel off the skin. Cut the cucumber in half lengthwise. Use a small spoon to scoop out and discard the watery seeds in the center.
8547cdd2-d0a2-4b58-9f79-0635f2b7ae1a Roughly chop or slice the peeled and seeded cucumber.
8547cdd2-d0a2-4b58-9f79-0635f2b7ae1a Put the chopped cucumber in a large glass container with a tight-fitting lid.
8547cdd2-d0a2-4b58-9f79-0635f2b7ae1a Pour the vodka over the cucumber. Seal the jar and let sit in a cool, dark space for at least three days and up to two weeks (any longer and the vodka will take on a slightly bitter taste).
8547cdd2-d0a2-4b58-9f79-0635f2b7ae1a Strain the vodka back into its original bottle or another clean bottle. Discard or eat what can now be considered the "pickled" cucumber whose flavor was infused into the vodka.
5da11a07-92b3-4a07-8169-25f3ec878370 Gather the ingredients.
5da11a07-92b3-4a07-8169-25f3ec878370 Pour the ingredients into a highball glass with ice cubes.
5da11a07-92b3-4a07-8169-25f3ec878370 Stir well.
5da11a07-92b3-4a07-8169-25f3ec878370 Garnish with a lime wedge.
1af5655d-8499-44b1-a152-55d297faaeb3 Gather the ingredients.

31c069ca-b757-480c-bb6a-a466d75c2a92 Shake well.
31c069ca-b757-480c-bb6a-a466d75c2a92 Strain into the cocktail glass.
b9ae36c1-f980-477b-af05-5fda32e6e903 Gather the ingredients.

b9ae36c1-f980-477b-af05-5fda32e6e903 In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the elderflower liqueur and pear vodka.

b9ae36c1-f980-477b-af05-5fda32e6e903 Strain into the prepared glass.

fd75fc18-a193-496a-9bc9-fef9d54875f7 Gather the ingredients.

fd75fc18-a193-496a-9bc9-fef9d54875f7 Top with equal amounts of cranberry and pineapple juices.
fd75fc18-a193-496a-9bc9-fef9d54875f7 Garnish with a lime wedge. Serve and enjoy!
365d842e-5149-4915-bcaa-2adf7a58d4df Gather the ingredients.
365d842e-5149-4915-bcaa-2adf7a58d4df Pour the vodka and grapefruit juice into a collins glass filled with ice cubes.
365d842e-5149-4915-bcaa-2adf7a58d4df Stir well.
365d842e-5149-4915-bcaa-2adf7a58d4df Garnish with a lemon or lime wedge. Enjoy.
ba628c99-97d0-4236-a2b2-22e9cd352b4d Gather the ingredients.
ba628c99-97d0-4236-a2b2-22e9cd352b4d Pour all ingredients except the rum in a highball glass.
ba628c99-97d0-4236-a2b2-22e9cd352b4d Stir.
ba628c99-97d0-4236-a2b2-22e9cd352b4d Float the rum on the top.
ba628c99-97d0-4236-a2b2-22e9cd352b4d Ignite with a match and extinguish before drinking.
ba628c99-97d0-4236-a2b2-22e9cd352b4d Serve and enjoy!
f3d213f2-f42e-4558-ab86-6d6f76e68c56 Gather the ingredients.
f3d213f2-f42e-4558-ab86-6d6f76e68c56 Beat the egg yolks, 1/4 cup of the sugar, salt, vanilla, and nutmeg (if using) together until it is very thick and has a light yellow color.
f3d213f2-f42e-4558-ab86-6d6f76e68c56 Slowly beat in the brandy and milk.
f3d213f2-f42e-4558-ab86-6d6f76e68c56 Cover and chill overnight in the refrigerator.
f3d213f2-f42e-4558-ab86-6d6f76e68c56 Shortly before serving, beat the egg whites to soft peaks.
f3d213f2-f42e-4558-ab86-6d6f76e68c56 Gradually beat in the remaining 1/4 cup sugar and beat this mixture to soft peaks again, creating a meringue-like cream.
f3d213f2-f42e-4558-ab86-6d6f76e68c56 Slowly pour this cream over the chilled brandy mixture, folding it in gently.
f3d213f2-f42e-4558-ab86-6d6f76e68c56 Serve the eggnog in a mug, Irish coffee glass, or punch cup and grate nutmeg over the top for a garnish. Enjoy.
74883b1c-08d6-4f2a-91a0-73f558ff21cd Gather the ingredients.
74883b1c-08d6-4f2a-91a0-73f558ff21cd Add the pisco, simple syrup, lime juice, and egg white to a cocktail shaker.
74883b1c-08d6-4f2a-91a0-73f558ff21cd Add ice to fill, and shake vigorously. Alternatively, you can use a blender if you don't have a shaker.
74883b1c-08d6-4f2a-91a0-73f558ff21cd Strain into an old-fashioned glass and sprinkle the Angostura bitters on top of the foam.
74883b1c-08d6-4f2a-91a0-73f558ff21cd Serve immediately.
5aec2054-c9e2-4657-b9fb-cbb71a7dfea1 Gather the ingredients.
5aec2054-c9e2-4657-b9fb-cbb71a7dfea1 Pour the ingredients into a cocktail shaker filled with ice cubes.
5aec2054-c9e2-4657-b9fb-cbb71a7dfea1 Shake well.
5aec2054-c9e2-4657-b9fb-cbb71a7dfea1 Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
5aec2054-c9e2-4657-b9fb-cbb71a7dfea1 Garnish with a lemon twist. Enjoy.
a2d7f784-9e16-47e4-a3f9-d77d47447f1c Gather the ingredients.
a2d7f784-9e16-47e4-a3f9-d77d47447f1c Beat the egg yolks, salt, and sugar until the mixture is thickened.
a2d7f784-9e16-47e4-a3f9-d77d47447f1c Slowly trickle in the brandy or cognac, but keep beating until it is well-blended.
a2d7f784-9e16-47e4-a3f9-d77d47447f1c Pour the mixture into a saucepan and warm over a low heat, continuously whisking. It is important to be patient. The advocaat is ready when it's nicely thickened and hot, but not boiling. If it boils, the alcohol will evaporate, and you'll lose a lot of the flavor and half the fun.
a2d7f784-9e16-47e4-a3f9-d77d47447f1c When the mix is thickened and very hot, remove the saucepan from the heat and whisk in the vanilla extract.
a2d7f784-9e16-47e4-a3f9-d77d47447f1c Allow the advocaat to cool and then place in the refrigerator until you're ready to serve in small glasses or espresso cups.
a2d7f784-9e16-47e4-a3f9-d77d47447f1c Top with whipped cream and a bit of cocoa powder to serve in the traditional manner or just serve with whipped cream or plain. Enjoy!
c65c884c-783c-4992-9cff-062e09246a9f Gather the ingredients.
c65c884c-783c-4992-9cff-062e09246a9f Build the drink in a brandy snifter by pouring the brandy and Grand Marnier into the glass. Serve and enjoy!
95ba794f-4901-4b5a-8376-1ace296225a7 Gather the ingredients.
95ba794f-4901-4b5a-8376-1ace296225a7 Pour the ingredients into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
95ba794f-4901-4b5a-8376-1ace296225a7 Shake vigorously for 30 seconds.
95ba794f-4901-4b5a-8376-1ace296225a7 Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
95ba794f-4901-4b5a-8376-1ace296225a7 Serve and enjoy!
87641281-cb33-4d80-a951-4e1e65e00cfb Gather the ingredients.
87641281-cb33-4d80-a951-4e1e65e00cfb Build the ingredients in an old-fashioned glass filled with ice.
87641281-cb33-4d80-a951-4e1e65e00cfb Stir and serve.
87641281-cb33-4d80-a951-4e1e65e00cfb Enjoy!
1aad9790-790a-4c40-b65e-2f6d7aae42d6 Gather the ingredients.
1aad9790-790a-4c40-b65e-2f6d7aae42d6 In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, add the brandy, sweet vermouth, simple syrup, and bitters.
1aad9790-790a-4c40-b65e-2f6d7aae42d6 Shake well.
1aad9790-790a-4c40-b65e-2f6d7aae42d6 Strain into a chilled cocktail glass. Serve and enjoy.
e9129cfb-ccca-4f65-a01b-cac29a97acda Gather the ingredients.
e9129cfb-ccca-4f65-a01b-cac29a97acda Place the sugar cube in the bottom of an old-fashioned glass. Saturate the cube with a splash of soda and the bitters, then add orange slices and cherries.
e9129cfb-ccca-4f65-a01b-cac29a97acda Muddle the ingredients.
e9129cfb-ccca-4f65-a01b-cac29a97acda Add the brandy and stir well.
e9129cfb-ccca-4f65-a01b-cac29a97acda Add a single, large piece of ice (such as an ice ball) and top with lemon-lime soda.
e9129cfb-ccca-4f65-a01b-cac29a97acda Serve and enjoy!

91f26a84-bb56-4954-a21b-8dc1ebc28cee Shake well.

91f26a84-bb56-4954-a21b-8dc1ebc28cee Garnish with a maraschino cherry.
2914a4a2-ea8e-4af2-a12b-dc29468a3360 Gather the ingredients.
2914a4a2-ea8e-4af2-a12b-dc29468a3360 Muddle the mint, sugar (or syrup), and club soda in an old-fashioned glass.
2914a4a2-ea8e-4af2-a12b-dc29468a3360 Fill the glass with ice cubes.
2914a4a2-ea8e-4af2-a12b-dc29468a3360 Add the brandy and stir well.
2914a4a2-ea8e-4af2-a12b-dc29468a3360 Garnish with an orange slice and cherry.
71e3431b-33b1-429e-b6b1-2ccf7b70807a Gather the ingredients.
71e3431b-33b1-429e-b6b1-2ccf7b70807a In a cocktail shaker filled with ice cubes, pour the brandy, crème de cacao, and cream. Shake well.
71e3431b-33b1-429e-b6b1-2ccf7b70807a Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
71e3431b-33b1-429e-b6b1-2ccf7b70807a Garnish with a dusting of nutmeg. Serve and enjoy.
50a27000-15f1-423a-8e5b-5b833d11554e Place the pisco, simple syrup, frozen mango chunks, Key lime juice and egg white in a blender.
50a27000-15f1-423a-8e5b-5b833d11554e Mix until they are smooth.
50a27000-15f1-423a-8e5b-5b833d11554e Serve in an old-fashioned glass or tumbler.
30f8f8c6-971c-4674-8263-4ca59609926b Gather the ingredients.
30f8f8c6-971c-4674-8263-4ca59609926b Sterilize two 1-quart jars and lids by boiling in water for 2 minutes. Let air dry on a clean, lint-free dish towel and set aside until needed.
30f8f8c6-971c-4674-8263-4ca59609926b Use a small, sharp knife to cut a small X shape at the base of each peach. Place peaches in a large, deep heatproof bowl and cover with boiling water. Allow peaches to sit for 2 to 3 minutes.
30f8f8c6-971c-4674-8263-4ca59609926b Using tongs, transfer one peach to a plate. Try to peel the skin off. If it comes off easily, then drain and peel the remaining peaches. If not, let them sit in the boiling water for a further minute or so.
30f8f8c6-971c-4674-8263-4ca59609926b Peel the peaches and cut in half and remove the pits. Cut each half into 4 pieces, so each peach yields 8 slices.
30f8f8c6-971c-4674-8263-4ca59609926b Arrange peaches in layers in the jars alternating layers of caster sugar. Place half of a split vanilla bean down the side of each jar.
30f8f8c6-971c-4674-8263-4ca59609926b Pour over the brandy making sure the peaches are completely covered. Seal tightly then shake gently to help dissolve the sugar.
30f8f8c6-971c-4674-8263-4ca59609926b Place jars in a cool, dark place for 3 months. Make sure you shake the jar gently once a week.
30f8f8c6-971c-4674-8263-4ca59609926b After 3 months serve brandied peaches with pancakes, ice cream or enjoy with a dollop of clotted cream for dessert.
30f8f8c6-971c-4674-8263-4ca59609926b Enjoy!
89ab3c82-b7a1-4925-8078-efab325872ab Gather the ingredients.
89ab3c82-b7a1-4925-8078-efab325872ab In a cocktail shaker, add the brandy, anisette, curaçao, and egg yolk.
89ab3c82-b7a1-4925-8078-efab325872ab Dry shake (without ice) vigorously.
89ab3c82-b7a1-4925-8078-efab325872ab Add ice and shake again, until the outside of the shaker is ice-cold and frosty.
89ab3c82-b7a1-4925-8078-efab325872ab Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
89ab3c82-b7a1-4925-8078-efab325872ab Serve and enjoy!

87473f3c-a71a-4a23-a573-3491a89a5b62 Stir well.

87473f3c-a71a-4a23-a573-3491a89a5b62 Garnish with grated nutmeg and dark chocolate.

1a45da88-310b-4937-b176-669a36c1b61a Stir well.

d7163074-5e03-4997-b9ed-78af9b0affd7 Pour the brandy, port, and orange juice into a cocktail shaker filled with ice.
d7163074-5e03-4997-b9ed-78af9b0affd7 Shake well.

b7581dac-14b6-4a47-b957-7ebc7c048640 Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.

b7581dac-14b6-4a47-b957-7ebc7c048640 Serve and enjoy!

c0fdd91d-9413-4bfb-8c24-eab2f04c9700 Add ice and stir for one minute.
c0fdd91d-9413-4bfb-8c24-eab2f04c9700 Strain into a chilled cocktail glass.
c0fdd91d-9413-4bfb-8c24-eab2f04c9700 Squeeze an orange peel over the drink, making sure the oils fall into the glass, then drop the peel into the drink.
0a903e95-0fce-435d-a675-22f178bf3ca3 Gather the ingredients.
0a903e95-0fce-435d-a675-22f178bf3ca3 In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the brandy, rum, simple syrup, milk, and optional vanilla extract and egg white.
0a903e95-0fce-435d-a675-22f178bf3ca3 Shake well (if you choose to add egg, shake until it hurts).
0a903e95-0fce-435d-a675-22f178bf3ca3 Strain into an old-fashioned glass with or without crushed ice.
0a903e95-0fce-435d-a675-22f178bf3ca3 Dust with grated nutmeg for garnish.
0a903e95-0fce-435d-a675-22f178bf3ca3 Serve and enjoy!

5a44a2f8-2add-4a68-b911-0cba2e4006a0 Add ice and shake well.
5a44a2f8-2add-4a68-b911-0cba2e4006a0 Strain into an old-fashioned glass with fresh ice cubes.
5a44a2f8-2add-4a68-b911-0cba2e4006a0 Float the chocolate syrup and cherry brandy on top by pouring them over the back of a bar spoon.

d3f0107b-d4e4-4a41-9287-8dd7dccf7b47 In a wine or old-fashioned glass filled with crushed ice, build the ingredients.

e2f9235a-bc86-4754-a4d0-9af29fa9dbfe Gather the ingredients.
e2f9235a-bc86-4754-a4d0-9af29fa9dbfe In separate cups, measure the rum, coffee liqueur, and brewed coffee and have at hand the spices.
e2f9235a-bc86-4754-a4d0-9af29fa9dbfe Using the sugar and lemon juice, rim a heat-resistant wine glass. Place the lemon juice in a shallow bowl and the sugar in another. Dip the rim of the glass into the lemon juice and then, while it's still wet, dip it into the sugar.
e2f9235a-bc86-4754-a4d0-9af29fa9dbfe Pour the rum into the wine glass.
e2f9235a-bc86-4754-a4d0-9af29fa9dbfe With extreme care, tilt the glass at a ​45-degree angle. With a long match or lighter, light the rum on fire, keeping it away from your face and hair. Don't be startled if it lights on fire before the fire touches the rum—this is normal. Return the glass to its vertical position and place it on a flat surface. If you used a match to light the fire, blow the match out. With your hand flat and facing down toward the table, hold the stem of the glass firmly between your index and middle fingers. Moving your hand in a circular motion, swirl the flaming rum in the glass to caramelize the sugar. Once the sugar is mostly caramelized, sprinkle the ground nutmeg and cinnamon over the drink. The spices will flavor the drink and add exciting visual sparks to the preparation of your cocktail.
e2f9235a-bc86-4754-a4d0-9af29fa9dbfe Quickly and carefully pour the desired liqueur on top of the cocktail. Do not worry if the liquid is boiling at first. It will cool down as you add more ingredients. Add the coffee. Add this point the glass should be 2/3 full.
e2f9235a-bc86-4754-a4d0-9af29fa9dbfe After the fire is out, your cocktail is complete. However, you can choose one or more of the optional garnishes to finish it off.
e2f9235a-bc86-4754-a4d0-9af29fa9dbfe It might still be hot, so enjoy with care!
ce266696-273d-4ac4-818f-5fd5320e6d8d Gather the ingredients.

ce266696-273d-4ac4-818f-5fd5320e6d8d Secure the lid and shake the jar so everything is combined.
ce266696-273d-4ac4-818f-5fd5320e6d8d Set in a cool, dark place and allow it to infuse for 2 to 3 days. Shake it once a day and give it a taste test on the second day to see how the flavor's developing. Do this daily until it reaches your desired taste.
ce266696-273d-4ac4-818f-5fd5320e6d8d Once you like the flavor, strain out the spices and fruit using a fine mesh strainer or cheesecloth, squeezing or pressing out any excess liqueur.

0929a8b5-3f40-4167-8d7f-8ebb1522f74c Gather the ingredients.

0929a8b5-3f40-4167-8d7f-8ebb1522f74c Bring to the boil, frequently stirring until the sugar is dissolved.

0929a8b5-3f40-4167-8d7f-8ebb1522f74c Cover the pan entirely and set aside for five days.
0929a8b5-3f40-4167-8d7f-8ebb1522f74c Sterilize and dry 2 or 3 wine or screwcap bottles.
0929a8b5-3f40-4167-8d7f-8ebb1522f74c Pass the apricot mixture through a fine sieve or a piece of muslin into a large bowl, keeping the apricots. Press the mixture well to remove as much juice as possible.

0929a8b5-3f40-4167-8d7f-8ebb1522f74c Wait for the minimum of one month before opening, but as with all liqueurs, it will improve the longer it sits.

0ff98dfd-0fb1-4f59-9787-a566930be9ae Melt the chocolate. The chocolate does not need to actually cook at all, just melt completely. Use one of the following methods: Microwave method: Place chocolate and heavy cream in a microwave safe bowl. Cook in microwave for a minute or so, making sure to stir every 20 seconds. Stop microwaving when mixture is smooth. Direct stove-top method: Place chocolate and cream in saucepan over low heat. Stir constantly until mixture is smooth. (Note: Be very careful when using this method, as a moment of inattention can lead to the chocolate´s burning). Hot water bath method: Place chocolate and cream in a metal bowl. Place the bowl in pan of very hot water in such a way that the water comes 1/3 to ½ way up the sides of the bowl. Stir ingredients gently until mixture is smooth.
0ff98dfd-0fb1-4f59-9787-a566930be9ae Stir in the cinnamon, coffee liqueur, and sugar. Pour into a serving dish and enjoy. Any leftover sauce can be stored in a tightly-covered glass jar in the refrigerator for a week or so. Reheat before using.

9882e351-54f8-431b-afb5-c2a1124adf0e Cut the lemons in half. Using a paring knife and spoon, carefully hollow out the insides.
9882e351-54f8-431b-afb5-c2a1124adf0e Add the lemonade to a pot or deep pan and sprinkle the gelatin over the juice. Let it sit for 2 minutes to "bloom." You’ll see a ripply film form on the top.
9882e351-54f8-431b-afb5-c2a1124adf0e Place the mixture on low heat. Heat and continually whisk until the gelatin evenly dissolves, about 2 to 5 minutes. Be careful not to let the mixture come to a boil.
9882e351-54f8-431b-afb5-c2a1124adf0e Remove from heat and let cool a bit. Stir in the vodka. At this point, you can also add a few drops of pink food coloring to get a deeper pink color.
9882e351-54f8-431b-afb5-c2a1124adf0e Place the lemon halves face up in a muffin tin. Pour the mixture into lemon halves.
9882e351-54f8-431b-afb5-c2a1124adf0e Refrigerate until set, 4 to 24 hours.
9882e351-54f8-431b-afb5-c2a1124adf0e Carefully cut the lemons into wedges and serve.

ae450297-61ad-47ee-9436-d4406ea64635 Spray a silicone mini muffin or candy-making pan (cavity volume = 2 to 4 tablespoons) lightly with cooking spray. Wipe the excess spray from the pan so there is no visible residue.
ae450297-61ad-47ee-9436-d4406ea64635 Pour lemonade into a small pot or deep pan and sprinkle with both packets of gelatin. Let sit for about 2 minutes until gelatin “blooms.” You’ll see a ripple film form on the top.​
ae450297-61ad-47ee-9436-d4406ea64635 Put the mixture on a low heat. Heat and continually whisk until the gelatin evenly dissolves about 2 to 5 minutes. Be careful not to let the mixture come to a boil.
ae450297-61ad-47ee-9436-d4406ea64635 Remove from heat and let the mixture cool a bit. Whisk in the vodka and sweetened condensed milk.
ae450297-61ad-47ee-9436-d4406ea64635 Divide the mixture evenly into 6 separate bowls. Put a few drops of different colored food coloring in each and whisk to thoroughly mix.
ae450297-61ad-47ee-9436-d4406ea64635 Spoon about 1 teaspoon of the first color mixture into the pan cavities. Refrigerate until set, usually about 20 minutes. But not too long because if they are sticky all the layers will set together better.
ae450297-61ad-47ee-9436-d4406ea64635 Repeat with all colors, letting each layer set for about 15 minutes. Refrigerate overnight.
8094bea1-c863-4808-925b-da7a3b7ebfa0 Gather the ingredients.

8094bea1-c863-4808-925b-da7a3b7ebfa0 Add the unflavored gelatin and let it sit for about 3 minutes.
8094bea1-c863-4808-925b-da7a3b7ebfa0 Add boiling water, stirring until the gelatin is completely dissolved. Stir in a few drops of food coloring if you want to customize the color.
8094bea1-c863-4808-925b-da7a3b7ebfa0 Pour into shot glasses, molds, or a baking pan for a sheet of gelatin to cut up after it sets.
8094bea1-c863-4808-925b-da7a3b7ebfa0 Refrigerate until the liquid sets up; at least 2 hours, but overnight is recommended.
8094bea1-c863-4808-925b-da7a3b7ebfa0 Serve cold and enjoy!

083ca1cb-db57-4ddf-bfc5-6e565c5fa1df Cut apples in half, down the stem. Using a paring knife and melon baller hollow out the center being careful not to puncture the skin.
083ca1cb-db57-4ddf-bfc5-6e565c5fa1df Brush the inside and edges of the cup apples thoroughly with lemon juice to prevent browning. Placing them face down will also help.
083ca1cb-db57-4ddf-bfc5-6e565c5fa1df Pour the cider into a small pot or deep pan. Sprinkle both packets of gelatin on top and let it sit for about 2 minutes to ‘bloom’. You’ll see a ripply film form on the top.
083ca1cb-db57-4ddf-bfc5-6e565c5fa1df Place the mixture on low heat. Heat and continually whisk until the gelatin evenly dissolves, about 2-5 minutes. Be careful not to let the mixture come to a boil. Then whisk in the melted caramel. Once everything is evenly combined, remove from the heat and let cool a bit.
083ca1cb-db57-4ddf-bfc5-6e565c5fa1df Add vodka and stir to thoroughly combine.
083ca1cb-db57-4ddf-bfc5-6e565c5fa1df Place the apple halves in a muffin tin, facing up. Pour the mixture into each hollowed-out apple.
083ca1cb-db57-4ddf-bfc5-6e565c5fa1df Refrigerate until firm, 4 to 24 hours.
083ca1cb-db57-4ddf-bfc5-6e565c5fa1df Cut the apple halves carefully into wedges and serve.

f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 Gather the ingredients.
f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 Prep your muffin pan or baking dish by lightly spraying it with cooking spray and then wiping out any excess or residue.

f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 Sprinkle the gelatin on top and let sit for at least 2 minutes to "bloom." You'll see a ripply film form on the top.
f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 Heat the mixture on medium-low heat and whisk continually until the gelatin is dissolved. Be careful not to let the mixture come to a boil.
f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 Remove from heat. Add in remaining lemon-lime soda and let cool a bit.
f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 Add a few drops of food coloring and stir to mix.
f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 Pour the mixture into the cavities of your muffin pan or into the baking dish.
f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 Refrigerate for 4 to 24 hours to set.
f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 The shots should slide easily out of the muffin pan but you may need to do some careful prodding with a small offset spatula. If using a baking pan, cut the jello into squares and then carefully remove.
f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 Dip the tops into a shallow bowl of sanding sugar.
f28f8bd3-c09c-461f-b467-8b400e8a20a7 Arrange the shots on a tray and let the fun begin.

00ecd814-fb6c-48ba-b212-238a217c4fa6 Gather the ingredients.
00ecd814-fb6c-48ba-b212-238a217c4fa6 Pour the Irish cream into a shot glass, then top it with Irish whiskey.
00ecd814-fb6c-48ba-b212-238a217c4fa6 In a tall pint glass, pour 1/2 a pint of Guinness and allow the foam to settle.
00ecd814-fb6c-48ba-b212-238a217c4fa6 When it's time to drink, drop the shot glass into the Guinness and drink as fast as you can.
00ecd814-fb6c-48ba-b212-238a217c4fa6 Enjoy!
f36c733b-6d57-4132-a17e-cadce092bac7 Gather the ingredients.
f36c733b-6d57-4132-a17e-cadce092bac7 In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the tequila and Ty Ku. Add a dash of sour mix.
f36c733b-6d57-4132-a17e-cadce092bac7 Shake well.
f36c733b-6d57-4132-a17e-cadce092bac7 Strain into a shot glass.
f36c733b-6d57-4132-a17e-cadce092bac7 Serve and enjoy!
139f5bf6-1407-4a55-9670-750025f385b0 Gather the ingredients.
139f5bf6-1407-4a55-9670-750025f385b0 Pour the grenadine into a shot glass.
139f5bf6-1407-4a55-9670-750025f385b0 Float the tequila on top of the grenadine.
139f5bf6-1407-4a55-9670-750025f385b0 Float the creme de menthe on top of the tequila.
d3dd51e5-4b57-4327-81c8-ef70d4841c6d Gather the ingredients.
d3dd51e5-4b57-4327-81c8-ef70d4841c6d Pour the crème de menthe into a shot glass.
d3dd51e5-4b57-4327-81c8-ef70d4841c6d Float the Irish cream liqueur on top of the crème de menthe by pouring it slowly over the back of a bar spoon.
d3dd51e5-4b57-4327-81c8-ef70d4841c6d Float the Grand Marnier on top of the Irish cream liqueur, again using the back of a bar spoon.
d3dd51e5-4b57-4327-81c8-ef70d4841c6d Do not stir. Serve as is, making sure not to jostle the cocktail too much so the colors don't bleed into each other.
d3dd51e5-4b57-4327-81c8-ef70d4841c6d Enjoy!
5a6eb60e-0d02-4e0c-b276-e351ac5ebcb6 Gather the ingredients.
5a6eb60e-0d02-4e0c-b276-e351ac5ebcb6 In a large punch bowl, combine the lychee and blue curaçao liqueurs, then top it with seltzer.
5a6eb60e-0d02-4e0c-b276-e351ac5ebcb6 Add ice if you like, otherwise, place the bowl in a tray of ice and let it chill. Garnish with orange slices.
5a6eb60e-0d02-4e0c-b276-e351ac5ebcb6 Serve and enjoy!
4a776510-2b28-4241-8d6a-4ad99e15ae7f Gather the ingredients.
4a776510-2b28-4241-8d6a-4ad99e15ae7f Fill a punch bowl halfway with ice.
4a776510-2b28-4241-8d6a-4ad99e15ae7f Add the ingredients and mix well.
4a776510-2b28-4241-8d6a-4ad99e15ae7f Serve in punch cups over ice.
4a776510-2b28-4241-8d6a-4ad99e15ae7f Garnish with strawberry slices.
4a776510-2b28-4241-8d6a-4ad99e15ae7f Serve and enjoy!
7fa1ede0-75ad-4f9a-a9d6-a6813a4f289a Gather the ingredients.
7fa1ede0-75ad-4f9a-a9d6-a6813a4f289a In a punch bowl, combine the partially thawed fruit punch, strawberries, orange and lemon juices, and water to create the fruit juice base.
7fa1ede0-75ad-4f9a-a9d6-a6813a4f289a Stir well and store in the refrigerator until you're ready to serve.
7fa1ede0-75ad-4f9a-a9d6-a6813a4f289a Just before serving the punch, add the ginger ale and Champagne.
7fa1ede0-75ad-4f9a-a9d6-a6813a4f289a Garnish with fresh strawberries, rosemary, seasonal fruit, or citrus slices.
7fa1ede0-75ad-4f9a-a9d6-a6813a4f289a Serve and enjoy!
c71143e2-84ed-4572-b71f-45cfb7bd37f2 Gather the ingredients.
c71143e2-84ed-4572-b71f-45cfb7bd37f2 Pour the ingredients into a mixing glass filled with ice cubes. Shake well.
c71143e2-84ed-4572-b71f-45cfb7bd37f2 Strain into a highball glass filled with ice cubes.
c71143e2-84ed-4572-b71f-45cfb7bd37f2 Top with club soda if you like and garnish with seasonal fruits.
c71143e2-84ed-4572-b71f-45cfb7bd37f2 Serve and enjoy!
373e516e-c63e-42f9-af8f-ec88531482a9 Gather the ingredients.
373e516e-c63e-42f9-af8f-ec88531482a9 In a large pitcher, combine the elderflower liqueur, cranberry and lemon juices, and simple syrup.
373e516e-c63e-42f9-af8f-ec88531482a9 Stir well and refrigerate overnight.
373e516e-c63e-42f9-af8f-ec88531482a9 When it's time for service, pour the spiked juice mix into a punch bowl and top with sparkling wine and soda.
373e516e-c63e-42f9-af8f-ec88531482a9 Garnish with cranberries, seasonal fruit, or citrus slices.
373e516e-c63e-42f9-af8f-ec88531482a9 Serve and enjoy!
1e62b6b7-3611-4ae1-a5e5-101e56322698 In a large pitcher, combine all of the ingredients.
1e62b6b7-3611-4ae1-a5e5-101e56322698 Add a handful of ice and stir well. Refrigerate until it's time to serve.
1e62b6b7-3611-4ae1-a5e5-101e56322698 Right before the party, add an ice ring or large cubes of ice to your punch bowl.
1e62b6b7-3611-4ae1-a5e5-101e56322698 Fill it with the pre-mixed punch and add seasonal berries.
1e62b6b7-3611-4ae1-a5e5-101e56322698 To serve, add a sprig of rosemary to each glass, fill it with fresh ice, then add a ladle full of punch. Be sure to include a few berries as well.
05d3af1b-628b-47ea-9916-bdfa6db5cb73 In a pitcher, dissolve sugar in the white wine, gin and grape juice.
05d3af1b-628b-47ea-9916-bdfa6db5cb73 Add grapes and apple slices and chill overnight.
05d3af1b-628b-47ea-9916-bdfa6db5cb73 Add ice and top with ginger ale or club soda prior to serving.
272adffd-b0aa-4f77-8943-6dc23b57e718 Gather the ingredients.
272adffd-b0aa-4f77-8943-6dc23b57e718 Place a frozen ice ring or large chunks of ice and some of the fresh fruit in a punch bowl.
272adffd-b0aa-4f77-8943-6dc23b57e718 Add all of the ingredients except the wine and soda and stir well.
272adffd-b0aa-4f77-8943-6dc23b57e718 Slowly add the ginger ale and Champagne.
272adffd-b0aa-4f77-8943-6dc23b57e718 Garnish with pomegranate seeds and other seasonal fruit, mint, or citrus slices.
272adffd-b0aa-4f77-8943-6dc23b57e718 Ladle into individual serving glasses, including a few fruits in each. Serve and enjoy.
d721b370-079a-4102-a552-a65625d6b993 Gather the ingredients.
d721b370-079a-4102-a552-a65625d6b993 In a large punch bowl or pitcher, combine the rum, red wine, lime juice, triple sec, simple syrup, and lime and orange slices.
d721b370-079a-4102-a552-a65625d6b993 Cover with plastic wrap and place in the refrigerator for at least two hours before serving (overnight is better).
d721b370-079a-4102-a552-a65625d6b993 Serve over ice in punch glasses and enjoy!
2cc1c309-b15b-4fe0-b592-9fd28ccb0c65 Gather the ingredients.
2cc1c309-b15b-4fe0-b592-9fd28ccb0c65 Pour the cherry whiskey, strawberry liqueur, and passion fruit into a punch bowl with large balls of ice. Have a bottle of Champagne on ice beside the punch bowl.
2cc1c309-b15b-4fe0-b592-9fd28ccb0c65 To serve, ladle the mixture into Champagne flutes and top with Champagne.
2cc1c309-b15b-4fe0-b592-9fd28ccb0c65 Garnish each glass with a strawberry or lemon twist on the rim.
2cc1c309-b15b-4fe0-b592-9fd28ccb0c65 Serve and enjoy!
86481427-6a23-4e8d-abc0-a44d45dad3e8 Combine bourbon and cider in a medium saucepan.
86481427-6a23-4e8d-abc0-a44d45dad3e8 Add lemon, cloves, allspice and cinnamon sticks.
86481427-6a23-4e8d-abc0-a44d45dad3e8 Heat over medium-high heat until the surface of the liquid almost begins to bubble.
86481427-6a23-4e8d-abc0-a44d45dad3e8 Pour into an Irish coffee glass.
86481427-6a23-4e8d-abc0-a44d45dad3e8 Garnish with a cinnamon stick.
8cbd1720-2d4f-4fd7-934d-1af2de8378db Gather the ingredients.
8cbd1720-2d4f-4fd7-934d-1af2de8378db In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour all of the ingredients.
8cbd1720-2d4f-4fd7-934d-1af2de8378db Shake well.
8cbd1720-2d4f-4fd7-934d-1af2de8378db Strain into a sour or highball glass.
8cbd1720-2d4f-4fd7-934d-1af2de8378db Serve and enjoy!
3624a30a-7ba6-4481-a58e-c1f34713ac6f Break the eggs into a large bowl.
3624a30a-7ba6-4481-a58e-c1f34713ac6f Add zest to eggs and beat with hand mixer until the eggs are frothy.
3624a30a-7ba6-4481-a58e-c1f34713ac6f Pour in evaporated and condensed milk and rum. Add bitters and nutmeg and beat until well blended and everything is incorporated.
3624a30a-7ba6-4481-a58e-c1f34713ac6f Strain and pour into distilled bottles, cork, and chill ideally for 24 hours or longer.
3624a30a-7ba6-4481-a58e-c1f34713ac6f Serve over ice.
a1930f11-c807-4194-95f1-49a6e00243e9 Gather the ingredients.
a1930f11-c807-4194-95f1-49a6e00243e9 In a large saucepan on low heat, add the gin and Madeira wine.
a1930f11-c807-4194-95f1-49a6e00243e9 Cut the lemon twists, orange slice, and pineapple chunks. Add them to the punch.
a1930f11-c807-4194-95f1-49a6e00243e9 Stir in the honey and lemon juice, then the cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon, and brown sugar. Continue stirring until the sugar and ground spices are dissolved.
a1930f11-c807-4194-95f1-49a6e00243e9 Simmer on low heat for 20 minutes.
a1930f11-c807-4194-95f1-49a6e00243e9 Strain using a fine-mesh strainer to remove all the whole fruits and spices. Pour the punch into a heat-proof punch bowl. Garnish with orange slices studded with cloves.
a1930f11-c807-4194-95f1-49a6e00243e9 Serve and enjoy!
22375f88-6379-49e0-82db-866c52d8ea82 Gather the ingredients.
22375f88-6379-49e0-82db-866c52d8ea82 In a cocktail shaker filled with ice, pour the white rum, orange liqueur, fruit juices, and grenadine.
22375f88-6379-49e0-82db-866c52d8ea82 Shake well.
22375f88-6379-49e0-82db-866c52d8ea82 Strain into a highball glass filled with fresh ice.
22375f88-6379-49e0-82db-866c52d8ea82 Slowly float the dark rum on top.
22375f88-6379-49e0-82db-866c52d8ea82 Serve and enjoy!
d522a81a-6f76-4a2d-8d02-8ee3c906cda2 Gather the ingredients.
d522a81a-6f76-4a2d-8d02-8ee3c906cda2 Slice the orange and lemons about 1/8-inch thick and place them in a large punch bowl.
d522a81a-6f76-4a2d-8d02-8ee3c906cda2 Add 1/2 cup of sugar (or less if you prefer) and let the fruit sit in the sugar for about 10 minutes, just long enough so that the fruit releases its natural juices.
d522a81a-6f76-4a2d-8d02-8ee3c906cda2 Add the wine and mix thoroughly to dissolve the sugar.
d522a81a-6f76-4a2d-8d02-8ee3c906cda2 Add the triple sec and the brandy and stir.
d522a81a-6f76-4a2d-8d02-8ee3c906cda2 Add the 2 cans of soda and stir (if you are making this ahead of time, don’t add the soda until your guests are about to arrive). Taste for sweetness. If desired, add more sugar or soda. Make sure that the sugar is completely dissolved.
d522a81a-6f76-4a2d-8d02-8ee3c906cda2 Add lots of ice to the punch bowl to chill completely. If you are serving in pitchers, fill with ice and then pour the sangria over the ice.
fff99673-c25e-4a67-9785-c01157ffb366 Gather the ingredients.
fff99673-c25e-4a67-9785-c01157ffb366 Combine the ingredients in a punch bowl and stir well.
fff99673-c25e-4a67-9785-c01157ffb366 Serve the punch in ice-filled glasses, garnishing each with a lime twist.
fff99673-c25e-4a67-9785-c01157ffb366 Serve and enjoy!
3afea1a1-12ff-440d-93f6-d094ba6cfcfa Gather the ingredients.
3afea1a1-12ff-440d-93f6-d094ba6cfcfa In a large pitcher or punch bowl with ice, pour the vodka, tequila, rum, gin, orange juice, and sports drink. Stir well.
3afea1a1-12ff-440d-93f6-d094ba6cfcfa Add a splash of cola, stir the punch, and add a little more if needed to get a "tea" color.
3afea1a1-12ff-440d-93f6-d094ba6cfcfa Serve and enjoy!
edd29b63-8c47-4dc6-a390-ebd3ae08fa2c Gather the ingredients.
edd29b63-8c47-4dc6-a390-ebd3ae08fa2c Place 2 quarts sliced strawberries in a medium bowl. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar or to taste. Wash the 2 lemons and zest them. Then squeeze out the juice. Add both the juice and zest to the strawberries and let sit for 2 hours in the refrigerator.
edd29b63-8c47-4dc6-a390-ebd3ae08fa2c Drain and reserve the strawberry juice. Add 1 bottle dry white wine to the strawberries and marinate in the refrigerator for 1 hour, or until the guests start arriving. Transfer the marinated strawberries to a punch bowl, and add the reserved strawberry juice and stir. Pour the 1 bottle of sparkling white wine into the bowl and serve.
edd29b63-8c47-4dc6-a390-ebd3ae08fa2c To serve, ladle punch and strawberries into the glass, garnish with a sprig of fresh mint or fresh lemon balm, if desired, and serve with a cocktail pick, so that the guests can eat the strawberries.
e04eb979-c9fa-4268-84a7-2b6cceb66ec6 Gather the ingredients.
e04eb979-c9fa-4268-84a7-2b6cceb66ec6 In a medium-sized pot on the stove, combine all of the ingredients.
e04eb979-c9fa-4268-84a7-2b6cceb66ec6 Over medium heat, warm the mixture, stirring regularly. It should take just 10 minutes or so, but you can turn down the heat to let it brew longer (the flavor gets better with time).
e04eb979-c9fa-4268-84a7-2b6cceb66ec6 Transfer to a large heatproof punch bowl. Serve in coffee mugs or Irish coffee glasses, garnishing each drink with shaved nutmeg.
e04eb979-c9fa-4268-84a7-2b6cceb66ec6 Serve and enjoy!
d1082d47-34bb-47f5-ac86-631f989c4b3e Gather the ingredients.
d1082d47-34bb-47f5-ac86-631f989c4b3e In a saucepan, combine the water and spices. Simmer over low heat for 10 minutes, without allowing it to reach a boil. Stir occasionally.
d1082d47-34bb-47f5-ac86-631f989c4b3e Add the sherry and sugar and continue to heat and stir for a few minutes, ensuring the sugar dissolves completely. Remove from the heat.
d1082d47-34bb-47f5-ac86-631f989c4b3e In small bowl, beat the egg yolks. Beat the egg whites in a separate bowl.
d1082d47-34bb-47f5-ac86-631f989c4b3e Stir the warm sherry mix and egg yolks together in a heat resistant punch bowl or wassail bowl.
d1082d47-34bb-47f5-ac86-631f989c4b3e Add the brandy.
d1082d47-34bb-47f5-ac86-631f989c4b3e Whisk in the egg whites until foamy.
d1082d47-34bb-47f5-ac86-631f989c4b3e Garnish the punch bowl with apple or other fruit slices.
d1082d47-34bb-47f5-ac86-631f989c4b3e Serve and enjoy!
fd0d22ac-f3e9-421c-9a46-642a90a7a9d5 Gather the ingredients.
fd0d22ac-f3e9-421c-9a46-642a90a7a9d5 Pour the Midori, rums, juices, and simple syrup into a punch bowl and mix well.
fd0d22ac-f3e9-421c-9a46-642a90a7a9d5 Garnish with the apple slices, blueberries, and melon balls.
fd0d22ac-f3e9-421c-9a46-642a90a7a9d5 Serve and enjoy!
e30356eb-f8df-41c8-9596-9f6d00beeaa9 Gather the ingredients.
e30356eb-f8df-41c8-9596-9f6d00beeaa9 In a large pot, heat the water, brandy, and spices, bringing the mixture to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
e30356eb-f8df-41c8-9596-9f6d00beeaa9 Stir in the wine, vodka, and sugar, and simmer for 1 minute.
e30356eb-f8df-41c8-9596-9f6d00beeaa9 Strain out the cloves and orange peel and decant the glögg, leaving the other spices behind.
e30356eb-f8df-41c8-9596-9f6d00beeaa9 Add raisins and almonds to each glass upon serving.
e30356eb-f8df-41c8-9596-9f6d00beeaa9 Serve and enjoy!
7eb25c1a-fa99-4288-88ff-d028173ac301 Gather the ingredients.
7eb25c1a-fa99-4288-88ff-d028173ac301 In a blender, crush 3/4 cup of ice.
7eb25c1a-fa99-4288-88ff-d028173ac301 Add all of the liquid ingredients.
7eb25c1a-fa99-4288-88ff-d028173ac301 Blend on high speed for 5 seconds.
7eb25c1a-fa99-4288-88ff-d028173ac301 Pour into a tall glass, adding more ice cubes until full.
7eb25c1a-fa99-4288-88ff-d028173ac301 Garnish with a sprig of mint.
7eb25c1a-fa99-4288-88ff-d028173ac301 Serve and enjoy!
